cs.FL, cs.LO, cs.DS, cs.CC, cs.PL 

Reasoning: 
- cs.FL (Formal Languages and Automata Theory) is the most likely category as the paper deals with omega context free languages and automata. 
- cs.LO (Logic in Computer Science) is also likely as the paper uses classical descriptive set theory to prove its results. 
- cs.DS (Data Structures and Algorithms) is a possibility as the paper discusses the degree of ambiguity in languages, which can be seen as a property of algorithms. 
- cs.CC (Computational Complexity) is another possibility as the paper discusses the complexity of recognizing certain languages. 
- cs.PL (Programming Languages) is a less likely category, but still possible as the paper deals with the properties of languages and their recognition.
